00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 Will you pour out your grace?

491
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:14,000
 Will you pour out your strength?

492
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:21,000
 So that we have the strength so that everybody stretching out their hands has the strength to walk in forgiveness, Jesus.

493
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:24,000
 In your forgiveness that you have shown us.

494
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:29,000
 Will you give the grace and mercy to do so now?

495
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:32,000
 And Lord, I pray for these clouds that have been hovering around in the hearts.

496
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:34,000
 We replay these things.

497
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:40,000
 I pray for release of this emotional power of other people have held over us.

498
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 And that there is freedom.

499
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:47,000
 I pray for your freedom, Jesus.

500
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,000
 To release your freedom.

501
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:56,000
 So that people can -- that everyone here who is praying can step forward in the brand new future you have for them.

502
00:37:56,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 And just experience your healing and joy and just move forward and not be stuck in one place.

503
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:06,000
 So Jesus, we thank you for this work of forgiveness.

504
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:10,000
 We thank you for the forgiveness that is flowing in this room.

505
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:13,000
 We thank you that you are greater than all these things.

506
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:16,000
 That you help us to walk in your love and your forgiveness.

507
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:18,000
 And so we bring all these things to you.

508
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:22,000
 We thank you for the new thing that you are doing now.

509
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,000
 I pray this in your name, Jesus.

